Sentencas: Composite cathodes consisting of -La1.6Sr0.4NiO4 (LSN) and -Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.9, (CGO) has been prepared for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SOFC).
Titulo: Preparation and electrochemical properties of composite cathode La1.6Sr0.4NiO4-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.9 for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: The chemical stability, microstruetures and electrochemical performance of the cathode have been investigated using XRD, SEM and AC impedance spectroscopy.
Titulo: Preparation and electrochemical properties of composite cathode La1.6Sr0.4NiO4-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.9 for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: Results showed that strong bonding was formed between the composite electrodes and CGO electrolytes after the electrodes were fired at 1050 degrees C for 4 hours.
Titulo: Preparation and electrochemical properties of composite cathode La1.6Sr0.4NiO4-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.9 for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: The polarization resistance changed with oxygen partial pressure, suggesting that charge transfer process was the rate limiting step for electrochemical oxygen reduction at the composite cathodes.
Titulo: Preparation and electrochemical properties of composite cathode La1.6Sr0.4NiO4-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.9 for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: Area specific resistance (ASR) for a LSN-40CGO composite cathode was 0.76 Omega (.)
Titulo: Preparation and electrochemical properties of composite cathode La1.6Sr0.4NiO4-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.9 for IT-SOFC

Titulo: Preparation and electrochemical properties of composite cathode La1.6Sr0.4NiO4-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.9 for IT-SOFC
